*Fix the Green Dragon Scale Issue***</span><hr size=1> Basically, only way to get them to correct the massive problem they created, is to keep making posts on forums and making replies when others do (yeah, they do forum trolling too), keep sending suggestions/comments to developers corner, sending feedback, and just basically sending email in general.  Compared to most other classes, there really aren't that many forums that are used by the warrior class, so we seem to them to not be as bothered as the other classes, who have done the same thing for the same problems (yeah, some call it whining).<br>
<br>
Main thing to do is keep your language down, in other words don't use language that your mother's threatened/used soap on you when you were a little kid.  Just rationally explain the situation and problems, use examples.  Remind them as they themselves have said that the warrior epic is one of the most difficult to obtain, and then turn around and show how warrior epic isn't as class changing as some of the other epics.  Let me see if I can dig up an old segment I have used on one occassion where things were really getting to my nerves:<br>
<br>
--------<br>
<br>
Warrior epic, is far from being a mega powerful and major class enchancing item, such as can be found on other epics.  Besides the basic stats that everyone has, you just need to start looking at effects to see that, even though warrior epic is in the top 2 or 3 in sheer difficulty to finish, it isn't something that unbalances play.  First, take a look at the other epics that have been made easier and/or have had triggered mobs added.  <br>
<br>
Cleric epic, by far the most powerful and in my book one of the easiest to obtain.  The only part of cleric epic that was really a hard portion was getting ragefire.  Once you were able to get Ragefire spawn before someone else came rushing in with bigger meaner force, the dragon is a sheer whimp to kill.  But the Revivisence effect, massively alters the game for the clerics who have epic, no mana to use, click click click, super fast CR in comparison to those relying on mana.  Finally, the cleric epic is the most numerous in the entire game, in terms of who has epics (not talking proportion of number of people in cleric class, just talking numbers of epics alone).  Now, the cleric epic has been made eaiser, merchant ragefire spawns every 24 hours instead of up to 72 hours, and then they trundle off to skyfire where they can have forces ported right to the zone for the fight and dragon is still the same level whimp he was before.<br>
<br>
Second, druid epic, two major and significant changes made this epic way easier.  The first change, the dragon Fay used to be on same type of timer as Severilous, 3/7, but the bottleneck grew to such proportions and the shear number of druids on server waiting for dragon caused all sorts of nasty races and ks'ings that Verant put in a triggered version of Fay which eliminated this problem (can trigger up to every 5 or 6 hours every day as long as someone doesn't screw up and fail...easy dragon to kill).  <br>
<br>
The second druid change involved adding the Venril Sathir Remains, since real VS doesn't live very long with the type of loot he has on him mega guilds would usually rush in and kill as soon as servers were up or he spawned leaving out 95 percent of druids and rangers needing the epic item, this was also a major change for rangers.  VSR was added and dropped 2 epic items, now rangers and druids both have a major part of epic out of the way, and VSR is way way way easier to kill than the real thing.  Once triggered fay killed and VSR killed, the rest of druid epic is a cakewalk and can be finished with just one group for fights.  Druid epic effect drastically changes the class in terms of just being able to get solo exp quick and easy, still making them the top 1 or 2 classes for rapid advancement/leveling.  One click and you have the second most powerful and rarely resisted dot in the game at work for you, with no mana cost, and just use your mana for snare, root and stacking the Ro line of dot and what do you have?  One dead mob faster than some groups can deal damage with mobs, in 60 seconds, dots alone have done over 2600 damage and not one heal was needed.<br>
<br>
As mentioned above, VSR made ranger epic much easier to obtain, leaving just the item from hate standing in the way of finishing the second blade of their epics.  So ranger effects on weapons, perma haste of 40 percent on one blade, frees up a slot for better item with stats than haste belt or cloak, and second epic weapon procs a slow, 20 percent I believe, making them both a faster attacker and slowing down mob attacks a good amount (less damage by mobs).  I have seen rangers being able to solo mobs so much easier when equipped with both epics than any warrior could hope to survive without major healing or shaman/enchanter backing them.  Talk about a major class altering epic, and difficulty of ranger epic doesn't even come close to what we have to go through as warriors.<br>
<br>
Ah yes, let's not forget the bard epic.  Only thing that needs to be said of one of the smallest classes in EQ, Bard Trak pansy whimp compared to real Trak.  Not only is bard epic a weapon, but it massively enchances the bard song effects, which just happen to be able to effect entire group performance/abilities or even area effect songs.  Thereby affecting not just one class but everyone around them as well as mobs.  The better a bard is at twisting songs the more powerful this one epic becomes in how it determines outcomes, average bards can twist 2 songs, good bards can twist 3 songs, and best bards can consistently twist 4 songs with rarely a missed note.<br>
<br>
There have been other changes to epics even minor changes to warrior epic. Sure now when you kill maestro a hand is guaranteed to always drop, and sure queen in chardok always drops blade now instead of as a rare, but both of these were fixes in absurdities.  You still need to basically clear a plane to get to Maestro without having to fight a ton of adds, and Queen is still the same mean bitch and if you don't kill in less than 30 to 45 seconds there is still a high probability of wipe out with her very very nasty AE and you have to fight through a thick batch of the toughest mobs in Chardok just to get to her and have to watch respawns at same time.<br>
<br>
Warrior epic still requires you to essentially clear 3 planes to get to epic mobs.  Hate has either Maestro or Very Unpleasant Hand to contend with and one slip up is all that is needed for wipeout.  Plane of Air, you must clear all the way to the Spiroc Isle and then clear almost everything to kill Spiroc Lord who doesn't always drop blade.  Golems are on a 3 day timer in Fear, but to get to them you still have to clear most of the plane and even then the golem metal is a rare drop.  Red dragon scale, isn't too hard to get since there are like 4 sources, Naggy, Ragefire, Talendor, and Scalekeeper, but still having to kill dragon caliber mob to get.  Already mentioned problems of dealing with Queen who could toast many a dragon and boss mobs in EQ.<br>
<br>
Then there is the problem of the green dragon scale.  Choices are 2, Hoskar in VP who doesn't always drop scale and has a major undertaking of a quest just to get a key for each person to be able to zone in, and second and realistic choice for 99.9 percent of all warrior epics to get done is killing Severilous for green scale.  Sev isn't one of the pansy version dragons that other classes get to deal with, but a full level 60 with a double AE attack, an AE fear and an AE stun (Mr Sev, how would you like your stunned appetizer prepared), I love bards when dealing with Sev, and DMF is nice too.  Add on top of this, mega guilds racing to get scale for a lower warrior or twink in addition to the rest of us needing the scale as well, and you have a huge bottleneck that is getting really nasty in competition (more so than any of the other epics have faced).<br>
<br>
Our epic, does it match up to the other 1 or 2 most difficult epics in the game for reward, the mage and necro?  I have a 58 mage so I know first hand the difficulties in that epic as well, and I still believe warrior is slightly harder.  But mage epic is one of the most powerful in the game and significantly changes effectiveness for the class since mages are 80 percent pet power and 20 percent spell power, so mage epic equals the risk vs reward rightfully.  Necro duck epic, or as we like to refer to it the Aflac Epic is one major pain and one I personally am glad I will never have to do.<br>
<br>
Effect on warrior epic, does not create a massive change in the abilities of the warrior, like some of the classes above.  It doesn't increase the abilities of others around them.  It doesn't drastically change game play of various encounters, e.g cleric epic.  What does it do?  100 dd, ac and attack debuffer, in other words a taunt.  Warriors already have a good taunt, which only really has to compete with the agro build up of monks with epics dealing damage and rangers epics hasting the ranger and slowing mobs (ask any shaman what is the biggest taunt in the game and they will say any time they cast slow on a mob).<br>
